class Solution {
    public int[] constructRectangle(int area) {
        int w = (int) Math.sqrt(area);
        while (area % w != 0) {
            w--;
        }
        return new int[] { area / w, w };
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution starts by assuming the width is the square root of the area, then iteratively decreases the width until it finds a divisor of the area, ensuring L >= W and minimizing L - W.
